# CityFlow – Decision-Aware Routing on GrabMaps

CityFlow adds a decision layer on top of GrabMaps routing.

Instead of only showing the fastest route, it helps users choose routes based on:
- Speed (Fastest)
- Safety at Night (lighting + incident proximity)
- System Impact (traffic distribution)

## What it uses
- GrabMaps Routing API (ETA + geometry)
- Street lighting dataset (visibility proxy)
- Traffic incident data (disruption proxy)
- Flood alerts (global risk signal)

## Key idea
Routing engines optimise silently.

CityFlow makes trade-offs visible and helps users choose better decisions.

## Demo Notes
- Fastest: Live GrabMaps route
- Safer at Night: prioritises lighting and fewer disruptions
- Distribute Traffic: shows how demand can be spread across the network

